<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="359" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                            <head><seg type="margin">[47]</seg> *<hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Boutwell</persName>, Secretary of the Treasury,
                                    to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>, Secretary of
                                    State.</hi></head>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Treasury
                                        Department</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-05-10"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 10,
                                1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge your
                                letter of the 8th instant, respecting the steamer Quaker City, and
                                to advise you that, pursuant <pb facs="0795" n="781" xml:id="pg_781"/> to your request, the collector of customs was on that day
                                instructed to prevent the sailing of that vessel in violation of the
                                neutrality act.</p>
                            <p>Very respectfully,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>GEO. S. BOUTWELL,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Secretary of the
                                        Treasury.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamilton Fish</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>